What’s Next with Aki Anastasiou – South Africa’s most popular technology talk show – has launched two new seasons. The first new season is What’s Next presented by Accenture, which will focus on navigating the IT services and consulting landscape in South Africa. Kgomotso Lebele, the Managing Director and Technology Lead at Accenture in South Africa, kicked the season off recently with an excellent interview. Lebele will be followed by several influential speakers. The launch of What’s Next presented by Accenture was soon followed by the launch announcement of What’s Next Season 6, presented by SAP. What’s Next Season 6 is coming soon, and in partnership with SAP it will cover topics like cloud computing, finance, logistics, sales, blockchain, business software, and much more. As always, these topics will be discussed by the top South African experts in these fields. MyBroadband makes it easy for companies and their executives to get featured on What’s Next with Aki Anastasiou. For more information about the show and how to get featured, visit: What’s Next with Aki Anastasiou To see what What’s Next can offer your business and its executives, watch the interview with Kgomotso Lebele from Accenture below. <span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start"></span>